    <h3>Execution History</h3>
    <p>The "Executions" tab on the left sidebar is our dashboard for observability. Every time an active workflow runs,
        a record is dropped here.</p>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Success (Green):</strong> The workflow completed normally. We can click into it to see the exact
            JSON payload traveling between every single node at every step.</li>
        <li><strong>Error (Red):</strong> The workflow crashed. n8n highlights the exact node that threw the error. We
            can see the HTTP status code, the stack trace, and the exact data the node was processing when it died.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="plain-english-box">
        <strong>In Plain English:</strong> The Execution History is an automatically generated, visual stack trace with
        full memory dumps at every step. It turns a 2-hour debugging session into a 30-second fix.
    </div>

    <h3>The Credential Manager</h3>
    <p>Never hardcode API keys in HTTP Request nodes. n8n houses a secure Credential Manager (accessed via the left
        sidebar). We create a credential once (e.g., "Production Stripe Key"), and n8n encrypts it in the database
        using the <code>N8N_ENCRYPTION_KEY</code> we defined in Chapter 2.</p>
    <p>To use it, drop an HTTP node on the canvas, set Authentication to "Predefined Credential Type," and select our
        saved key. The API key is securely injected at runtime.</p>

